FBIS4-11941 "drnes064_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-064 Daily Report 2 Apr 1994 India President Accepts Resignations of 2 Ministers President Accepts Resignations of 2 Ministers BK0204101294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 2 Apr 94 BK0204101294 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The resignations of the minister of state for railways, Mr. K.C. Lenka, and the minister of state for finance and parliamentary affairs, Dr. Abrar Ahmed, have been accepted. According to a Rashtrapati Bhavan [President House] spokesman, the president, Dr. Shankar Dayal Sharma, accepted their resignations on the advise of the prime minister. The two ministers have tendered their resignations as they ceased to be members of the Rajya Sabha from today.
